@startuml
[*] as Initial State
state "User Login" as Login
state "Destination Selection" as Destination
state "Journey Details Displayed" as JourneyDetails
state "Driving Mode Activated" as DrivingMode
state "Place to Eat Selected" as PlaceToEat
state "Menu Viewed" as MenuViewed
state "Order Placed" as OrderPlaced
state "Accident Occurred" as Accident
state "Notifications Sent" as Notifications
state "Feedback Provided" as Feedback

Login --> Destination : User selects destination
Destination --> JourneyDetails : System displays journey details
JourneyDetails --> DrivingMode : User activates driving mode
DrivingMode --> PlaceToEat : User selects place to eat
PlaceToEat --> MenuViewed : User views menu
MenuViewed --> OrderPlaced : User places order
OrderPlaced --> Notifications : System sends notifications during driving
Notifications --> Accident : System detects accident
Accident --> Feedback : User provides feedback upon completion

[*] --> Login : Initial state
JourneyDetails --> [*] : Final state after journey details displayed
Feedback --> [*] : Final state after feedback provided
OrderPlaced --> [*] : Final state after order placed
Notifications --> [*] : Final state after notifications sent
Accident --> [*] : Final state after accident occurred

@enduml
